#. type: Title #
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:1
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Subaddress"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:7
msgid "Subaddress is what you should be using by default to receive Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Learn for what you are being paid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:11
msgid ""
"By providing a unique subaddress for each anticipated payment you will know "
"for what you are being paid."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:13
msgid ""
"This use case overlaps with integrated addresses. Subaddresses are generally "
"prefered for reasons outlined below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prevent payer from linking your payouts together"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:18
msgid ""
"To prevent the payer from linking your payouts together simply generate a "
"new subaddress for each payout.  This way specific service (like anonymous "
"exchange) that sends you Monero won't (easilly) know it is you again "
"receving Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:20
msgid ""
"The exception to this is when a service (or group of colluding services) "
"decides to actively attack you, one address at the time, with the so-called "
"[Janus attack](https://web.getmonero.org/2019/10/18/subaddress-janus.html), "
"which risks them losing funds. If you need perfect unlinkability of your "
"receivables, the only solution remains to use a separate seed (separate "
"Monero wallet)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:22
msgid ""
"Also, note it won't help if you have an account with the service. Then your "
"payouts are already linked in the service database, regardless of Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Group funds into accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Accounts** are a convenience wallet-level feature to group subaddresses under one label and balance.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:28
msgid ""
"You may want to organize your funds into accounts like \"cash\", \"work\", "
"\"trading\", \"mining\", \"donations\", etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:30
msgid ""
"As accounts are only groupings of subaddresses, they themselves do not have "
"an address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:32
msgid ""
"Accounts are deterministically derived from the root private key along with "
"subaddresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:34
msgid ""
"Accounts are similar to subaccounts in your classic bank account. There is a "
"very important difference though. In Monero funds don't really sit on "
"accounts or public addresses. Public addresses are conceptually a gateway or "
"a routing mechanism. Funds sit on transactions' unspent outputs. Thus, a "
"single transaction can - in principle - aggregate and spend outputs from "
"multiple addresses (and by extension from multiple accounts). The CLI or GUI "
"wallet may not directly support creating such transactions for simplicity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:36
msgid "In short, think of accounts as a **soft** grouping of your funds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Why not multiple wallets?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:41
msgid ""
"The advantage over creating multiple wallets is that you only have a "
"**single seed** to manage.  All subaddresses can be derived from the wallet "
"seed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:43
msgid ""
"Additionally, you conveniently manage your subaddresses within a single user "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wallet level feature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:47
msgid ""
"Subaddresses and accounts are a wallet-level feature to construct and "
"interpret transactions. They do not affect the consensus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data structure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:51
msgid "Subaddress has a dedicated \"network byte\":"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Index       | Size in bytes    | Description\n"
"------------|------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"0           | 1                | identifies the network and address type; [42](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L171) - mainnet; [36](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L200) - stagenet; [63](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L185) - testnet\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:57
msgid ""
"Otherwise the data structure is the same as for the [standard address](/"
"public-address/standard-address/#data-structure)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generating"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:61
msgid "Each subaddress conceptually has:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:64
msgid "account index (also known as \"major\" index)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:64
msgid "subaddress index within the account (also known as \"minor\" index)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:66
msgid "The indexes are 0-based. By default wallets use account index 0."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:69
msgid ""
"The indexes are not directly included in the subaddress data structure.  "
"Instead, they are used as input to generating subaddress keys."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "Private view key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:73
msgid "A per-subaddress scalar `m` is derived as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "    m = Hs(\"SubAddr\" || a || account_index || subaddress_index_within_account)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:77
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:94
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:106
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid ""
"`Hs` is a Keccak-256 hash function interpreted as integer and modulo `l` "
"(maximum edwards25519 scalar)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid "`||` is a byte array concatenation operator"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid "`SubAddr` is a 0-terminated fixed string (8 bytes total)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid ""
"`a` is a private view key of the standard address (a 32 byte little endian "
"unsigned integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid ""
"`account_index` is index of an account (a 32 bit little endian unsigned "
"integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
msgid ""
"`subaddress_index_within_account` is index of the subaddress within the "
"account (a 32 bit little endian unsigned integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:86
msgid ""
"Deriving \"sub view keys\" from the main view key allows for creating a view "
"only wallet that monitors the entire wallet including subaddresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Public spend key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:90
msgid "The subaddress public spend key `D` is derived as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "    D = B + m*G\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:98
msgid "`B` is standard address public spend key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:98
msgid ""
"`m` is a per-subaddress scalar that is derived from the private spend key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:98
msgid ""
"`G` is the \"base point\"; this is simply a constant specific to "
"[edwards25519](/cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Public view key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:102
msgid "The subaddress public view key `C` is derived as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "    C = a*D\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:109
msgid "`a` is a private view key of the standard address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:109
msgid "`D` is a public spend key of the subaddress"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "Special case for (0, 0)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:114
msgid ""
"The subaddress #0 on the account #0 is the [standard address](/public-"
"address/standard-address).  As standard address has different generation "
"rules, this is simply implemented via an `if` statement."
msgstr ""

